reviews.review: A worthy ending to the Skywalker saga. Has its flaws but definitely better than the last 2 movies.

I absolutely loved this film. Entertaining from beginning to end. Well-acted, unexpectedly emotional, and filled with some satisfying plot twists. The special effects and sound were spectacular and cane with expected chills only Star Wars can provide. Let the Force in and go see this film. I honestly do not understand the hate this film is getting. I saw the original many years ago when I was 5 and was filled with awe and wonder then. I feel the same after this one and I plan to see it again.

There are a few slow parts that seem unnecessary to tell the story and a few scenes that seem rushed. The ending of the film is a little confusing if you have not seen the first 6 movies but overall an enjoyable way to spend 2 and 1/2 hours
That was the most disappointing Star Wars movie I have ever seen. A mix of unoriginal ideas from the worst source material they could find in the Legends. It is a complete mess!

A must see if you saw any of the other movies of the trilogy. Or if you're a Star Wars fan in general. Highly recommended. The amount of emotion that overwhelms you, the ambience, the story arc, plot twists and explanations are all finished in the closing out of the 3rd trilogy. Hats off to J. J. Abrams, this movie is a must see.
Thus movie is everything The Last Jedi could have been. A fitting end to the saga we all grew up with

JJ Abrams did the best he could with what Rian Johnson left him.  I did not hate The Last Jedi,  I just think Abrams set up a potential amazing Episode 8 and Johnson flubbed it.  Having said that, Rise of Skywalker was very satisfying.  I wish there was more of a climactic fight scene with Emperor Palpatine and Rey.  No spoilers here so I wont go into detail.  The movie moved fast and had a lot of action.  Movie score was amazing.  I understand that Abrams cut a really good scene involving Darth Vader's Force Wraith... Lets hope they include it in the Blue Ray!

Critics are just too critical. I know it's their job and all, but let's think about something: this is a movie. It is a fictional piece of film made for entertainment. I was thoroughly entertained. Do I think it's the best movie ever? No. Do I think it was a very satisfying end to the Star Wars saga? Absolutely. If you're a Star Wars fan, my recommendation would be to turn off your film-critic eyes, and just go along for the ride. It was fun, frantic, and cool.... if you let it be. When you enter the theater, you only take what you have with you.
Fun but really rushed. You'll enjoy it if you don't feel like thinking too hard.
Not perfectâ€”too much squeezed in. But lots of fun and good story. Much better than the one before.
